# RGB Traffic Light

## Overview

This project simulates a traffic light system using an RGB LED connected to an Arduino Uno. The LED changes colors in a timed sequence to represent red, yellow, and green traffic signals.

## Components Used

- Arduino Uno
- RGB LED
- Resistors
- Jumper Wires

## Concepts Learned

- RGB LED control
- Digital Output
- Timing using `delay()`
- Sequential programming

## Files

- `RGB_Traffic_Light.ino` – Arduino source code
- `circuit.png` – Tinkercad circuit screenshot

## Future Improvements

- Add a pedestrian crossing button.
